<subSubSection id="92FF215E68084521C8F6F4F00051F1D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="BB2D8A3AAF8A4A87B127B64EC465ABB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7322A7DC2EB953A4F9A73F40532C285F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Vigorous twining or sprawling liana to 4 m; stems and all vegetative parts densely white-tomentose. Leaves petiolate, 8-20 
<normalizedToken id="FE03108EB63AB46BE42FC1BA2A4974B9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-20 cm, ovate to suborbicular, obtuse or acute, base subtruncate to shallowly cordate with rounded auricles, densely white-tomentose on both surfaces but abaxially paler; petioles 4-35 mm. Inflorescence of shortly pedunculate 3-6-flowered cymes borne on side branches so appearing to form elongate bracteate racemes; bracts resembling small leaves; peduncles very short, 0.5-3 cm, tomentose; bracteoles 10-20 
<normalizedToken id="5CB6A3FC821B30F00FFB3DEC6DCB705A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-6 mm, oblong-elliptic, caducous; pedicels 2-3.5 cm, sulcate, thickened upwards, tomentose; sepals 15-20 
<normalizedToken id="A23A52AFDFFEE06E88CE7F82EE23B03E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-10 mm at anthesis but strongly accrescent in fruit to 25 
<normalizedToken id="527598B2453CC451A659EA6A06EFED0A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15 mm, ovate to elliptic, obtuse, densely tomentose; corolla 6-10 cm long, white, subhypocrateriform, tomentose, more densely so on midpetaline bands, limb c. 5 cm diam., undulate. Capsules 20-25 
<normalizedToken id="04458D4A68B312A81D5801C922AC72AE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-18 mm, ovoid, glabrous; seeds 11-14 
<normalizedToken id="E381D1EE626B0F789595859468755474" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6 mm, black with long marginal hairs 12-20 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
